{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "lhs",
    "name": "lhs_user_weight_prim",
    "description": "Latin Hypercube Sampling sweep characterizing the (user_custody_fraction,\nuser_split) decision boundary identified by user_weight_threshold.yaml.\n\nMOTIVATION:\nThe 6\u00d75 threshold grid (30 scenarios) revealed that:\n  - 7/28 completed scenarios produced v26 wins (25%)\n  - v26 wins are concentrated in split \u2208 [0.30, 0.50] across multiple ucf levels\n  - The boundary is non-monotonic in ucf \u2014 v26 wins at ucf=0.10 but NOT 0.20,\n    then again at 0.35 and 0.65 (split=0.30 column)\n  - At ucf=0.65, split=0.50: complete v27 hashrate collapse (hr_v27=0%)\n  - split \u2265 0.60 is unconditionally v27 across all ucf levels tested\n  - The User-PRIM null result (Phase 3) is a calibration artifact, not structural\n\nThis sweep fills the contested (ucf, split) zone at ~3\u00d7 the grid density to:\n  1. Distinguish genuine boundary structure from stochastic variance\n  2. Identify whether the non-monotonicity in ucf is real or noise\n  3. Precisely locate the split threshold above which user weight becomes irrelevant\n  4. Provide n\u226560 labeled scenarios for logistic regression boundary fitting\n\nKNOWN BOUNDS (from user_weight_threshold.yaml):\n  Lower boundary (v26 onset in ucf): between 0.01 (v27) and 0.10 (v26) at split=0.30\n  Upper boundary (split safe zone):  between 0.50 (v26 wins) and 0.60 (v27 wins)\n  Most extreme v26 win: ucf=0.65, split=0.50 \u2192 hr_v27=0%, econ_v27=28.9%\n  Non-monotonic interior: ucf=0.10 v26, ucf=0.20 v27, ucf=0.35 v26 at split=0.30\n\nSAMPLING REGION RATIONALE:\n  user_custody_fraction [0.05, 0.70]:\n    - Lower 0.05: below confirmed v26-win floor, captures onset threshold\n    - Upper 0.70: slightly beyond max tested (0.65), confirms upper plateau behavior\n  user_split [0.25, 0.65]:\n    - Lower 0.25: below min tested (0.30), extends lower boundary\n    - Upper 0.65: extends into confirmed-v27 territory to anchor classifier boundary\n    - Transition zone [0.50, 0.60] deliberately oversampled by LHS density\n\nDESIGN:\n  - 60 scenarios via LHS (5 per namespace, 12 namespaces)\n  - 2D active parameter space only \u2014 all pool/econ params fixed at PRIM midpoints\n  - Identical fixed params to user_weight_threshold for direct comparability\n  - Seed 314 (distinct from Phase 3 seed 2026)\n\nRUNTIME (12 namespaces, full network):\n  - 60 scenarios / 12 namespaces = 5 per namespace\n  - ~3.6 hours per scenario (2016-block retarget, duration=13000s)\n  - ~18 hours wall-clock\n\nANALYSIS (tools/discovery/fit_boundary.py):\n  - Logistic regression on (ucf, split) \u2192 win/loss\n  - PRIM box on v26-win region to characterize contested zone\n  - Combined with threshold grid (n=28): total n=88 user-weight scenarios\n  - Decision rule: if logistic boundary is monotone in split, report clean threshold;\n    if non-monotone, report contour with confidence intervals\n",
    "spec_file": "tools/sweep/specs/lhs_user_weight_prim.yaml",
    "base_network": "full",
